external_knowledge:
- 'Position' in basketball refers to the role a player plays on the court, such as Point Guard (PG), Shooting Guard (SG), Small Forward (SF), Power Forward (PF), and Center (C);
- 'Annual salary' refers to the yearly compensation for the player;
- 'Top 5 positions' means the five positions with the highest average annual salaries.

- "team changes" refers to the number of times a player has changed teams;
- "average salary" is calculated over all contracts for the player;
- "total salary earned" is the sum of all salaries over the player's career;
- "last contract start" and "last contract end" refer to the most recent contract period;
- "injury count" is the total number of injuries a player has had;
- "total recovery time" is the sum of all recovery times for injuries;
- "avg recovery time" is the average recovery time for injuries;
- "contract duration" is the length of the most recent contract in years.

sql:
SELECT p.player_name, t.team_name AS current_team_name
FROM players p
INNER JOIN teams t ON p.current_team_id = t.team_id;

